  "decision_conditions": [
    "CONDITION: Details and samples of all facing materials shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to any work commencing on site.  The details shall include:\r\n\r\na) specific insulation to be used (including type and thickness);\r\n\r\nb) sample of render (showing colour, texture and method of application);\r\n\r\nc) detail drawing showing how the new insulation and render will be finished off where they meet the front elevation vertical brickwork joint; and\r\n\r\nd)  detail showing how existing coping over flank wall will be replaced to allow new coping to cover brickwork and insulation.\r\n\r\nThe development shall be carried out strictly in accordance with the details so approved and shall be maintained as such thereafter.\r\n\r\nREASON: In the interest of securing sustainable development and to ensure that the resulting appearance and construction of the development is of a high standard in accordance with policies 7.4 and 7.8 of the London Plan 2011, policies D4, D11, D24 and D42 of the Islington Unitary Development Plan 2002 and policies CS8, CS9 and CS10 of the Islington Core Strategy 2011 and the Chapel Market/Penton Street Conservation Area Design Guidelines."
